State Kapu Corporation Chairman Chalamasetti Ramanujaiah on Tuesday said it would be spending Rs. 100 crore every year for the welfare of Kapu, Balija and Telaga castes.Addressing the media, Mr. Ramanujaiah explained Chief Minister N. Chandrababu Naiduâ€™s plans to ensure the welfare of Kapus. He further said the corporation would focus on improving the standard of living of those earning their livelihood through sale of handicraft products.Besides, Mr. Ramanujaiah said a committee headed by Justice Manjunath would consider including Kapus on the BC list and submit a report to the State government on the matter. He added that the Corporation officials would tour the Rayalaseema districts to garner suggestions from people.